icecast
------------------------------------------
Icecast is a streaming media server which currently supports Ogg (Vorbis and
Theora), Opus, WebM and MP3 audio streams. It can be used to create an Internet
radio station or a privately running jukebox and many things in between. It is
very versatile in that new formats can be added relatively easily and supports
open standards for commuincation and interaction.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.0.7-1
  libcurl4-7.65.3-1
  libkate1-0.4.1-2
  libogg0-1.3.1-1
  libspeex1-1.2.0-2
  libssl1.1-1.1.1c-1
  libtheora0-1.1.1-2
  libvorbis0-1.3.6-1
  libxml2-2.9.9-2
  libxslt-1.1.29-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-10-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-6
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.icecast.org/

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.xiph.org/releases/icecast/icecast-2.4.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack icecast-2.4.4-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./icecast-2.4.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/icecast-2.4.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/icecast-2.4.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

